{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"isHeader":true,"content":"Preparation","step":0},{"isHeader":false,"content":"Preheat oven to 200°C. Dust a baking tray with flour then set aside.","step":1},{"isHeader":false,"content":"Place plain flour, wholemeal flour, salt and bicarbonate of soda in mixing bowl then mix <b>5 sec\/speed 5<b>.","step":2},{"isHeader":false,"content":"Add buttermilk and mix <b>25 sec\/speed 5.5<b>. Working quickly, tip the sticky dough out onto a floured surface and bring together into a ball. Place on prepared tray.","step":3},{"isHeader":false,"content":"Dust loaf with flour then, with a floured sharp knife cut a cross in the top of dough about 3 cm deep. Bake for 25-35 minutes (200°C) until loaf sounds hollow when tapped underneath. Transfer to a wire rack to cool before serving.","step":4}],"usefulItems":"baking tray, long sharp knife, wire rack, oven, oven","id":"r92997","imageLink":"https:\/\/4.bp.blogspot.com\/-xhlFxWZe0wU\/XZaongPh3aI\/AAAAAAAAhL4\/Fv2Nzq7x13IBjV_1-fwcKrv4FClk4mTVQCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_tkxP1rLHf5J9onEZ.png","title":"Irish Soda Bread","ingredients":[{"isHeader":true,"content":"Ingredients"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"250 g plain flour, plus extra for dusting"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"250 g wholemeal flour"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"1 ½ tsp fine sea salt"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"1 ½ tsp bicarbonate of soda"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"450 g buttermilk"}],"nutrition":["per 1 slice","521 kJ \/ 125 kcal","4.8 g","24.9 g","0.6 g"],"hintsAndTricks":["This tasty, slightly sweet, crumbly cake-like bread is really quick to make, thanks to the baking soda which is used as a leavening agent instead of yeast. There are several variations of soda bread to be found throughout different regions of Ireland - we’ve gone for a mixture of plain and wholemeal flours. A perfect accompaniment to a big bowl of steaming soup or simply enjoyed buttered with jam or lemon curd."],"basicInfo":["easy","5m","45m","16 slices"]}